"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"8a949619-8aae-4f1a-a46c-6bbf236c34b3\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01QWcVikRRTTTg2C5b3gJ3yT\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# E2E Tests\\n     2→\\n     3→End-to-end tests for the `entire` CLI against real agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Factory Droid, Kiro).\\n     4→\\n     5→## Commands\\n     6→\\n     7→```bash\\n     8→mise run test:e2e [filter]                          # run filtered (or omit filter for all agents)\\n     9→mise run test:e2e --agent claude-code [filter]       # Claude Code only\\n    10→mise run test:e2e --agent gemini-cli [filter]        # Gemini CLI only\\n    11→mise run test:e2e --agent opencode [filter]          # OpenCode only\\n    12→go build ./...                                      # compile check (no agent CLI needed)\\n    13→```\\n    14→\\n    15→**Do NOT run E2E tests proactively.** They make real API calls that consume tokens and cost money. Only run when explicitly asked.\\n    16→\\n    17→## Structure\\n    18→\\n    19→```\\n    20→e2e/\\n    21→├── agents/       # Agent abstraction (Agent interface, tmux sessions, concurrency gates)\\n    22→├── bootstrap/    # CI pre-test setup (auth config, warmup)\\n    23→├── entire/       # `entire` CLI wrapper (enable, rewind, etc.)\\n    24→├── exploratory/  # Experimental tests, not run by CI\\n    25→├── tests/        # Blessed test files (run by CI)\\n    26→└── testutil/     # Repo setup, assertions, artifact capture\\n    27→```\\n    28→\\n    29→## Key Patterns\\n    30→\\n    31→- Every test uses `testutil.ForEachAgent` which runs it per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling.\\n    32→- All operations go through `RepoState` (`s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`) so they're logged to `console.log`.\\n    33→- Use the `entire` package for CLI interactions, not raw `exec.Command`.\\n    34→- Skip tests pending CLI fixes with `t.Skip(\\\"ENT-XXX: reason\\\")`.\\n    35→\\n    36→## Adding a New Agent\\n    37→\\n    38→1. Create `agents/<name>.go` implementing the `Agent` interface.\\n    39→2. Register it in `init()` with `Register(&YourAgent{})`.\\n    40→3. Add a `Bootstrap()` method for any CI-specific setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    41→4. Add a `RegisterGate(\\\"<name>\\\", N)` call if concurrency needs limiting.\\n    42→5. Ensure the agent name is accepted by `mise run test:e2e --agent <name>`.\\n    43→6. Add the agent to `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` matrix and `e2e-isolated.yml` options.\\n    44→\\n    45→## Environment Variables\\n    46→\\n    47→| Variable | Description | Default |\\n    48→|----------|-------------|---------|\\n    49→| `E2E_AGENT` | Agent to test (`claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`, `factoryai-droid`, `kiro`) | all registered |\\n    50→| `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` | Path to a pre-built `entire` binary | builds from source |\\n    51→| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Timeout per prompt | `2m` |\\n    52→| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Set to `1` to preserve temp repos after test | unset |\\n    53→| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output directory | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n    54→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n    55→| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n    56→| `KIRO_AUTH_BUNDLE_B64` | Base64 tar.gz of Kiro auth files (GitHub secret for Kiro CI jobs) | — |\\n    57→\\n    58→## Debugging Failures\\n    59→\\n    60→Artifacts are captured to `e2e/artifacts/` on every run (git-log, git-tree, console.log, checkpoint metadata, entire logs). Set `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1` to preserve the temp repo — a symlink appears in the artifact dir pointing to it.\\n    61→\\n    62→Use the `debug-e2e` skill (`.claude/skills/debug-e2e/`) for a structured workflow when investigating failures.\\n    63→\\n    64→### Reading artifacts\\n    65→\\n    66→- `console.log` — full operation transcript including agent stdout/stderr\\n    67→- `git-log.txt` — commit history at time of failure\\n    68→- `git-tree.txt` — working tree state\\n    69→- `entire-logs/` — internal CLI logs\\n    70→\\n    71→### Fixing flaky tests\\n    72→\\n    73→When a test passes on retry but failed once, the problem is usually agent non-determinism, not a CLI bug. Common patterns:\\n    74→\\n    75→- **Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting**: The model output contains \\\"Does this look right?\\\" or \\\"Should I proceed?\\\". Fix: append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\" to the prompt.\\n    76→- **Agent wrote to wrong path or created extra files**: Fix: be more explicit about exact file paths and what _not_ to do.\\n    77→- **Agent committed when it shouldn't have**: Fix: add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to the prompt.\\n    78→- **Checkpoint wait timeout**: `WaitForCheckpoint` or `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom` exceeded deadline. Fix: increase the timeout argument.\\n    79→\\n    80→To diagnose: read `console.log` in the failing test's artifact directory. Compare what the agent actually did vs what the test expected.\\n    81→\\n    82→## CI Workflows\\n    83→\\n    84→- **`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** — Runs full suite on push to main. Matrix: `[claude-code, opencode, gemini-cli, factoryai-droid, kiro]`.\\n    85→- **`.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml`** — Manual dispatch for debugging a single test. Inputs: agent + test name filter.\\n    86→\\n    87→Both workflows run `go run ./e2e/bootstrap` before tests to handle agent-specific CI setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    88→\\n    89→## Kiro on GitHub-hosted CI\\n    90→\\n    91→Kiro requires login. For non-interactive GitHub-hosted runners:\\n    92→\\n    93→1. Generate a Kiro auth bundle with [`scripts/kiro-auth/create-auth-bundle.sh`](../scripts/kiro-auth/create-auth-bundle.sh).\\n    94→2. Upload the generated `.b64` output to the `KIRO_AUTH_BUNDLE_B64` GitHub secret.\\n    95→3. CI restores this bundle before bootstrapping/running Kiro tests.\\n    96→\\n    97→If Kiro jobs fail with `account: null`, rotate the secret by regenerating the bundle.\\n    98→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"abca7218-9a37-429e-847f-d81e233732e9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T19:07:58.965Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a0f69859fc1a7e8ed\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01RZLEMWM4zTLa9f6GfFcU1k\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01EZQovuCTvbmbYQviSz5UyX\",\"uuid\":\"b210900a-32d1-40c9-9d3e-4faf94629d45\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T19:07:59.334Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b210900a-32d1-40c9-9d3e-4faf94629d45\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"8a949619-8aae-4f1a-a46c-6bbf236c34b3\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T19:07:59.363Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_0193Kf69dF98ojFHqzLW3ob9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_016t5pbQxbHKD9WCdyYbhSw5\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/scripts/kiro-auth/README.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":14039,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":90818,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":14039},\"output_tokens\":24,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYgfwBJmrpRrrRPaGCuNN\",\"uuid\":\"506ec7de-b08e-4190-bac6-fbbbc91333b4\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId