(ctx context.Context) bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThere is no separate `HookHandler` interface. Hook handling is done through `ParseHookEvent` returning a normalized `*Event`, which is then dispatched by the generic `DispatchLifecycleEvent` in `hook_registry.go`.\\n\\n**Optional interfaces**: `FileWatcher`, `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `TranscriptPreparer`, `TokenCalculator`, `HookResponseWriter`, `SubagentAwareExtractor`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. The `Event` and `EventType` (`/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`)\\n\\n```go\\ntype EventType int\\n\\nconst (\\n    SessionStart  EventType = iota + 1\\n    TurnStart\\n    TurnEnd\\n    Compaction\\n    SessionEnd\\n    SubagentStart\\n    SubagentEnd\\n)\\n\\ntype Event struct {\\n    Type       EventType\\n    SessionID  string\\n    SessionRef string   // agent-specific transcript path\\n    Prompt     string   // for TurnStart\\n    Timestamp  time.Time\\n    // ... subagent fields, metadata, etc.\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Kiro Agent Identity and Key Characteristics (`kiro.go`)\\n\\n```go\\ntype KiroAgent struct{}\\n\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) Name() types.AgentName   { return agent.AgentNameKiro }   // \\\"kiro\\\"\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) Type() types.AgentType   { return agent.AgentTypeKiro }   // \\\"Kiro\\\"\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) IsPreview() bool         { return true }\\nfunc (k *KiroAgent) ProtectedDirs() []string { return []string{\\\".kiro\\\"} }\\n```\\n\\n**Detection**: checks for `.kiro/` directory in the repo root.\\n\\n**Session ID**: Kiro does NOT provide a session ID in hook stdin. The session ID is self-generated (32-char hex string) and cached to `.entire/tmp/kiro-active-session` at `agentSpawn` time, then read by subsequent hooks.\\n\\n**Transcript storage**: Kiro stores conversations in SQLite at:\\n- macOS: `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3`\\n- Linux: `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3`\\n\\nAt `stop`, the agent queries SQLite via `sqlite3` CLI (no CGO), caches the transcript to `.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json`, and sets `SessionRef` in the event to that path.\\n\\n**Test mock**: `ENTIRE_TEST_KIRO_MOCK_DB=1` skips SQLite, returns `\\\"mock-session-id\\\"` and pre-built paths.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. Kiro Hook Types and Names (`lifecycle.go`, `hooks.go`)\\n\\n**5 hooks total** (Kiro's camelCase → CLI's kebab-case subcommands):\\n\\n| Kiro Native Name | CLI Subcommand | Event Type | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `agentSpawn` | `agent-spawn` | `SessionStart` | Generates + caches session ID |\\n| `userPromptSubmit` | `user-prompt-submit` | `TurnStart` | Reads cached session ID, includes `prompt` |\\n| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil` | Pass-through, no lifecycle action |\\n| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil` | Pass-through, no lifecycle action |\\n| `stop` | `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Reads session ID cache, fetches SQLite transcript |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. Hook Installation: `InstallHooks` (`hooks.go`)\\n\\nKiro is unique: it **owns its file entirely** - no round-trip preservation needed (unlike Claude Code and Cursor which merge into existing files).\\n\\n**Config file**: `.kiro/agents/entire.json`\\n\\n**Written content**:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire\\\",\\n  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"read\\\", \\\"write\\\", \\\"shell\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"glob\\\", \\\"aws\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n            \\\"introspect\\\", \\\"knowledge\\\", \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"todo\\\", \\\"delegate\\\"],\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"agentSpawn\\\":       [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro agent-spawn\\\"}],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"}],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\":       [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\":      [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    \\\"stop\\\":             [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Idempotency**: If all 5 hooks are already present and not using `force`, returns `(0, nil)` early. The `allHooksPresent()` helper checks exact command matches.\\n\\n**Local dev mode**: Uses `go run ${KIRO_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks kiro <verb>` instead of `entire hooks kiro <verb>`.\\n\\n**File permissions**: Written at `0o600` (owner read/write only).\\n\\n**`UninstallHooks`**: Simply removes the whole `.kiro/agents/entire.json` file (idempotent, no error if missing).\\n\\n**`AreHooksInstalled`**: Reads the file, checks if any of `AgentSpawn`, `UserPromptSubmit`, or `Stop` has an Entire hook prefix (`\\\"entire \\\"` or the local-dev prefix). Returns `false` on JSON parse error.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. Contrast: How Claude Code and Cursor Install Hooks\\n\\n**Claude Code** (`claudecode/hooks.go`):\\n- Merges into `.claude/settings.json` (which has many other settings)\\n- Uses `map[string]json.RawMessage` for round-trip preservation of unknown fields\\n- Installs 7 hooks: `SessionStart`, `SessionEnd`, `Stop`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `PreToolUse(Task)`, `PostToolUse(Task)`, `PostToolUse(TodoWrite)`\\n- Also adds `permissions.deny` rule to block Claude from reading `.entire/metadata/`\\n- Hook structure is nested: `ClaudeHookMatcher{Matcher: \\\"\\\", Hooks: []ClaudeHookEntry{{Type: \\\"command\\\", Command: \\\"...\\\"}}}` \\n- Fully additive: only removes Entire hooks on `force` or uninstall\\n\\n**Cursor** (`cursor/hooks.go`):\\n- Merges into `.cursor/hooks.json` (may have other user hooks)\\n- Uses `map[string]json.RawMessage` for round-trip preservation\\n- Installs 7 hooks: `sessionStart`, `sessionEnd`, `beforeSubmitPrompt`, `stop`, `preCompact`, `subagentStart`, `subagentStop`\\n- Hook structure is flat: `CursorHookEntry{Command: \\\"...\\\"}` arrays per hook type\\n- Fully additive: preserves unknown hook types\\n\\n**Kiro** (`kiro/hooks.go`):\\n- Completely owns `.kiro/agents/entire.json` - writes from scratch every time\\n- Simple replacement strategy, no round-trip preservation\\n- 5 hooks with simpler `kiroHookEntry{Command: \\\"...\\\"}` structure\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. `entire enable` Flow (`setup.go`)\\n\\n```\\nentire enable [--agent kiro]\\n  └── newEnableCmd() → RunE\\n        ├── paths.WorktreeRoot() check (must be in git repo)\\n        ├── if --agent kiro:\\n        │     └── setupAgentHooksNonInteractive(ctx, w, kiroAgent, opts)\\n        │           ├── hookAgent.InstallHooks(ctx, localDev, forceHooks)  ← calls KiroAgent.InstallHooks\\n        │           ├── setupEntireDirectory()\\n        │           ├── strategy.InstallGitHook()   ← installs prepare-commit-msg etc.\\n        │           └── strategy.EnsureSetup()\\n        └── else (interactive):\\n              ├── detectOrSelectAgent() → shows multi-select TUI\\n              │     (only shows agents implementing HookSupport)\\n              └── runEnableInteractive(ctx, w, agents, opts)\\n                    ├── uninstallDeselectedAgentHooks()\\n                    ├── for each agent: setupAgentHooks() → hookAgent.InstallHooks()\\n                    ├── setupEntireDirectory()\\n                    ├── strategy.InstallGitHook()\\n                    └── strategy.EnsureSetup()\\n```\\n\\nThe `setupAgentHooks` function does the type assertion:\\n```go\\nfunc setupAgentHooks(ctx context.Context, ag agent.Agent, localDev, forceHooks bool) (int, error) {\\n    hookAgent, ok := ag.(agent.HookSupport)\\n    if !ok {\\n        return 0, fmt.Errorf(\\\"agent %s does not support hooks\\\", ag.Name())\\n    }\\n    count, err := hookAgent.InstallHooks(ctx, localDev, forceHooks)\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 8. Hook Dispatch Flow (`hooks_cmd.go`, `hook_registry.go`)\\n\\n**Registration** (`hooks_cmd.go`):\\n```go\\nfunc newHooksCmd() *cobra.Command {\\n    // imports _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro\\\" (triggers init())\\n    for _, agentName := range agent.List() {\\n        ag, _ := agent.Get(agentName)\\n        if handler, ok := ag.(agent.HookSupport); ok {\\n            cmd.AddCommand(newAgentHooksCmd(agentName, handler))\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Self-registration** via `init()` in `kiro/kiro.go`:\\n```go\\nfunc init() {\\n    agent.Register(agent.AgentNameKiro, NewKiroAgent)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Command tree built** (`hook_registry.go`):\\n```\\nentire hooks kiro\\n  ├── agent-spawn       → RunE calls KiroAgent.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"agent-spawn\\\", stdin)\\n  ├── user-prompt-submit → RunE calls KiroAgent.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"user-prompt-submit\\\", stdin)\\n  ├── pre-tool-use      → RunE calls KiroAgent.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"pre-tool-use\\\", stdin)\\n  ├── post-tool-use     → RunE calls KiroAgent.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"post-tool-use\\\", stdin)\\n  └── stop              → RunE calls KiroAgent.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"stop\\\", stdin)\\n```\\n\\n**Dispatch path** for each hook invocation:\\n```\\nKiro invokes: entire hooks kiro stop\\n  └── newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging(\\\"kiro\\\", \\\"stop\\\").RunE\\n        ├── paths.WorktreeRoot() check\\n        ├── IsEnabled() check\\n        ├── currentHookAgentName = \\\"kiro\\\"\\n        ├── handler.ParseHookEvent(ctx, \\\"stop\\\", cmd.InOrStdin())\\n        │     └── KiroAgent.parseStop() → reads session ID cache → queries SQLite → returns TurnEnd event\\n        └── if event != nil: DispatchLifecycleEvent(ctx, ag, event)\\n              └── strategy.SaveStep() or other lifecycle actions\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 9. Strategy-Level Git Hooks (`strategy/hooks.go`)\\n\\nThese are separate from agent hooks. The `strategy/hooks.go` installs shell scripts into `.git/hooks/`:\\n\\n- `prepare-commit-msg` → `entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg \\\"$1\\\" \\\"$2\\\"`\\n- `commit-msg` → `entire hooks git commit-msg \\\"$1\\\"`\\n- `post-commit` → `entire hooks git post-commit`\\n- `pre-push` → `entire hooks git pre-push \\\"$1\\\"`\\n\\nThese fire on git operations and are agent-agnostic. They handle checkpoint condensation, trailer injection (`Entire-Checkpoint: <id>`), and log pushing.\\n\\nKey function: `InstallGitHook(ctx, silent, localDev, absolutePath bool) (int, error)` — backs up pre-existing hooks to `.pre-entire`, chains them.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 10. Registry Wiring (`registry.go`)\\n\\nConstants added for Kiro:\\n```go\\nAgentNameKiro types.AgentName = \\\"kiro\\\"\\nAgentTypeKiro types.AgentType = \\\"Kiro\\\"\\n```\\n\\n`GetAgentsWithHooksInstalled(ctx)` (in `config.go`) iterates all registered agents, type-asserts each to `HookSupport`, and calls `AreHooksInstalled()`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary of the Kiro-Specific Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **File ownership**: Kiro owns `.kiro/agents/entire.json` entirely — written from scratch each time, not merged. Simpler than Claude Code and Cursor which do careful round-trip JSON preservation.\\n\\n2. **Session ID generation**: Kiro does not provide a session ID in hook stdin. The agent generates a 32-char hex random ID at `agentSpawn` time and caches it to `.entire/tmp/kiro-active-session`. Subsequent hooks read this file to maintain consistent session identity.\\n\\n3. **Transcript timing**: SQLite is only populated at `stop` time (when the turn ends), not at `agentSpawn` or `userPromptSubmit`. The transcript is fetched and cached to `.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json` only in the `stop` handler.\\n\\n4. **Pass-through hooks**: `preToolUse` and `postToolUse` are registered (the agent file has entries for them) but `ParseHookEvent` returns `(nil, nil)` for them — they serve as no-ops that the CLI silently ignores.\\n\\n5. **Tool list requirement**: The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools, or `--agent entire` restricts the model to zero tools.\\n\\n6. **Activation requirement**: Hooks only fire when `kiro-cli chat --agent entire` is passed. Without that flag, the entire.json file is ignored.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a4b3c6bfcd0e05118 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 149403\\ntool_uses: 28\\nduration_ms: 1180