"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01A5vR5wwkQjrju1gcnywZ6U\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Kiro Agent Integration\\n     2→\\n     3→Implementation one-pager for the Kiro (Amazon AI coding CLI) agent integration.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Identity\\n     6→\\n     7→| Field | Value |\\n     8→|-------|-------|\\n     9→| Package | `kiro` |\\n    10→| Registry Key | `kiro` |\\n    11→| Agent Type | `Kiro` |\\n    12→| Binary | `kiro-cli` |\\n    13→| Preview | Yes |\\n    14→| Protected Dir | `.kiro` |\\n    15→\\n    16→## Hook Events (5 total)\\n    17→\\n    18→| Kiro Hook (camelCase) | CLI Subcommand (kebab-case) | EventType | Notes |\\n    19→|----------------------|----------------------------|-----------|-------|\\n    20→| `agentSpawn` | `agent-spawn` | `SessionStart` | Agent initializes |\\n    21→| `userPromptSubmit` | `user-prompt-submit` | `TurnStart` | stdin includes `prompt` field |\\n    22→| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    23→| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    24→| `stop` | `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Checkpoint trigger |\\n    25→\\n    26→No `SessionEnd` hook exists — sessions end implicitly (similar to Cursor).\\n    27→\\n    28→## Hook Configuration\\n    29→\\n    30→**File:** `.kiro/agents/entire.json`\\n    31→\\n    32→We own the entire file — no round-trip preservation needed (unlike Cursor's shared `hooks.json`).\\n    33→\\n    34→**Format:**\\n    35→```json\\n    36→{\\n    37→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire\\\",\\n    38→  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"read\\\", \\\"write\\\", \\\"shell\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"glob\\\", \\\"aws\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n    39→            \\\"introspect\\\", \\\"knowledge\\\", \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"todo\\\", \\\"delegate\\\"],\\n    40→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    41→    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro agent-spawn\\\"}],\\n    42→    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"}],\\n    43→    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    44→    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    45→    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n    46→  }\\n    47→}\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→Note: The file is a Kiro agent definition. Hooks must be nested under the `hooks` field.\\n    51→Required top-level fields: `name`. Optional: `$schema`, `description`, `prompt`, `mcpServers`,\\n    52→`tools`, `toolAliases`, `allowedTools`, `resources`, `hooks`, `toolsSettings`, `model`, etc.\\n    53→\\n    54→**Important:** The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools. Without it, `--agent entire`\\n    55→restricts the model to zero tools. The tool names come from `~/.kiro/agents/agent_config.json.example`.\\n    56→\\n    57→## Agent Activation\\n    58→\\n    59→Hooks only fire when `--agent entire` is passed to `kiro-cli chat`. Without this flag,\\n    60→`.kiro/agents/entire.json` is not loaded and hooks do not execute.\\n    61→\\n    62→**`--no-interactive` mode:** Does not fire agent hooks. All E2E tests use interactive (tmux) mode.\\n    63→\\n    64→**TUI prompt indicator:** `!>` in trust-all mode (with `-a` flag). The `Credits:` line\\n    65→appears after each agent response and serves as a reliable completion marker.\\n    66→\\n    67→## Hook Stdin Format\\n    68→\\n    69→All hooks receive the same JSON structure on stdin:\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\n    72→  \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\",\\n    73→  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n    74→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user message\\\",\\n    75→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\",\\n    76→  \\\"tool_input\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    77→  \\\"tool_response\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    