pulated based on the hook event — `prompt` only for `userPromptSubmit`, tool fields only for tool hooks.\\n    82→\\n    83→## Transcript Storage\\n    84→\\n    85→**Source:** SQLite database at `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (macOS)\\n    86→or `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (Linux).\\n    87→\\n    88→**Table:** `conversations_v2`\\n    89→- `key` column: CWD path (used for lookup)\\n    90→- `value` column: JSON blob with conversation data\\n    91→- `updated_at` column: timestamp for ordering\\n    92→\\n    93→**Conversation JSON structure:**\\n    94→```json\\n    95→{\\n    96→  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid-v4\\\",\\n    97→  \\\"history\\\": [\\n    98→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}]},\\n    99→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"tool_use\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\", \\\"input\\\": {...}}]},\\n   100→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"request_metadata\\\", \\\"input_tokens\\\": 150, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 80}\\n   101→  ]\\n   102→}\\n   103→```\\n   104→\\n   105→## Session ID Discovery\\n   106→\\n   107→Hook stdin does not include session ID. We query SQLite by CWD:\\n   108→```sql\\n   109→SELECT json_extract(value, '$.conversation_id')\\n   110→FROM conversations_v2\\n   111→WHERE key = '<cwd>'\\n   112→ORDER BY updated_at DESC LIMIT 1\\n   113→```\\n   114→\\n   115→## SQLite Access Strategy\\n   116→\\n   117→Uses `sqlite3` CLI (pre-installed on macOS/Linux) rather than a Go library to avoid CGO dependencies. Same approach as OpenCode's `opencode export` CLI.\\n   118→\\n   119→**Test mock:** `ENTIRE_TEST_KIRO_MOCK_DB=1` env var causes the agent to skip SQLite queries and use pre-written mock files.\\n   120→\\n   121→## File Modification Tools\\n   122→\\n   123→Tools that modify files on disk:\\n   124→- `fs_write` — write file content\\n   125→- `