OMPT` for `promptSubmit`), not stdin.\\n- No `agentSpawn` IDE trigger exists. The first `promptSubmit` serves as session start.\\n- `AreHooksInstalled` returns true if EITHER CLI or IDE hooks are present.\\n- `InstallHooks` installs 9 hooks total (5 CLI + 4 IDE).\\n\\n## Hook Stdin vs Environment Variables\\n\\n| Hook source | Data delivery |\\n|-------------|---------------|\\n| CLI agent (`--agent entire`) | JSON on stdin |\\n| IDE extension (`.kiro/hooks/`) | Environment variables |\\n\\nThe lifecycle parser handles both by attempting stdin first, then falling back to env vars on empty stdin.\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Implementation Sequencing\\n\\n1. **`types.go`** first — the struct definitions are needed by everything else\\n2. **`hooks.go`** second — can be implemented and tested independently\\n3. **`lifecycle.go`** third — the stdin fallback\\n4. **`hooks_test.go`** — update existing tests + add new ones\\n5. **`lifecycle_test.go`** — update existing tests + add new ones\\n6. **`AGENT.md`** — documentation last\\n\\n### Potential Pitfalls and Edge Cases\\n\\n**Pitfall 1: Linter - `wrapcheck` on `os.WriteFile`**\\nThe `wrapcheck` linter requires wrapping errors from external packages. All `os.WriteFile`/`os.ReadFile` errors in the new helpers must be wrapped with `fmt.Errorf(\\\"...: %w\\\", err)`.\\n\\n**Pitfall 2: `forbidigo` on `os.Getwd`**\\nThe linter forbids `os.Getwd()`. The nolint directive with an explanation is required: `//nolint:forbidigo // Intentional: IDE hooks don't provide CWD in stdin`.\\n\\n**Pitfall 3: `gosec` on file paths**\\nNew `os.ReadFile` and `os.WriteFile` calls need `//nolint:gosec // path constructed from repo root + constant` comments, consistent with existing code.\\n\\n**Pitfall 4: `dupl` linter**\\nThe `installIDEHooks` helper and `allIDEHooksPresent` function share similar iteration patterns. If the duplication threshold (75 tokens) is triggered, add `//nolint:dupl // intentional: separate read vs write loops for IDE hook fil