*.kiro.hook)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe Kiro agent currently installs hooks only in `.kiro/agents/entire.json` (CLI agent definition format). This works for `kiro-cli chat --agent entire` but **not** for the Kiro IDE (VS Code extension), which reads hooks from `.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook` files. We need to install IDE hooks there while keeping the existing CLI agent hooks.\\n\\nKey difference: CLI hooks receive JSON on stdin. IDE hooks pass data via environment variables (`USER_PROMPT` for promptSubmit) with **no stdin**. The lifecycle parsers must handle empty stdin gracefully.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` — Add IDE hook types\\n\\nAdd 3 structs for the `.kiro.hook` file format:\\n\\n```go\\ntype kiroIDEHookFile struct {\\n    Enabled     bool            `json:\\\"enabled\\\"`\\n    Name        string          `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n    Description string          `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    Version     string          `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n    When        kiroIDEHookWhen `json:\\\"when\\\"`\\n    Then        kiroIDEHookThen `json:\\\"then\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype kiroIDEHookWhen struct {\\n    Type string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype kiroIDEHookThen struct {\\n    Type    string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    Command string `json:\\\"command\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — Install/uninstall/check IDE hooks\\n\\n**New constants and data:**\\n- `ideHooksDir = \\\"hooks\\\"` — directory within `.kiro`\\n- `ideHookFileSuffix = \\\".kiro.hook\\\"`\\n- `ideHookDefs` — slice of 4 definitions mapping filename → trigger type → CLI verb\\n\\n**IDE hooks to install (4 files):**\\n\\n| File | `when.type` | Command |\\n|------|-------------|---------|\\n| `entire-prompt-submit.kiro.hook` | `promptSubmit` | `entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit` |\\n| `entire-stop.kiro.hook` | `agentStop` | `entire hooks kiro stop` |\\n| `entire-pre-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `preToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use` |\\n| `enti